WEBVTT

00:00.802 --> 00:06.288
Well, it's good to be together this morning, good to be with you with you and really of those of you watching online.

00:06.329 --> 00:18.102
If you had the opportunity and the honor and the privilege that it is to sit in my seat, I'll tell you, you would be blown away by what God is doing in our church.

00:18.903 --> 00:27.954
This past week, we launched Alpha and Alpha's environment for people who are new to faith, exploring faith, because we want to be the easiest church to invite your friends

00:28.130 --> 00:32.455
And we've had so many people in Alpha in this session, we had to move them all to the big rooms.

00:32.955 --> 00:41.825
So we were in this room and also in the auditorium there in a really 190 people participating in Alpha in this season, which is unbelievable.

00:41.885 --> 00:42.185
Yeah.

00:46.930 --> 00:55.079
And all kinds of high school students at a really a location we actually saw the most high school students we've ever seen wanting to jump into group there.

00:55.139 --> 00:57.682
It's been amazing to see what God is doing.

00:57.922 --> 01:02.551
And meeting so many of you who would say, hey, I'm on the front edge of discovering faith.

01:02.711 --> 01:03.933
I'm asking questions.

01:04.074 --> 01:05.156
I'm here to explore.

01:05.837 --> 01:07.961
We really are here for you.

01:08.021 --> 01:13.371
And the interesting thing to me is just the power of the local church.

01:13.411 --> 01:21.266
And that's really what we're talking about in this series, that the local church is Jesus' movement, that we represent him on earth.

01:21.666 --> 01:26.053
that the Bible talks about you and I as the body of Christ when we come together.

01:26.093 --> 01:32.943
You might be a hand, I might be a foot, you might be the armpit, whatever it might be, but we all have a different role.

01:32.963 --> 01:37.950
We all have a different part that we play, but together we represent Jesus.

01:39.012 --> 01:43.198
And we talked the first week about, hey, what does it mean to actually reflect Jesus?

01:43.238 --> 01:46.202
If we are the body of Christ, what does it mean to look like Jesus?

01:46.242 --> 01:48.626
We should look like the Jesus who found us.

01:48.770 --> 01:51.734
The first week we looked at the personality of Jesus.

01:52.234 --> 01:59.563
And we looked at the fact that man, the church isn't just a club for the found, it's not that at all, it's a search party for the lost.

01:59.683 --> 02:12.159
And then last week we looked at the posture of Jesus and the fact that there's no bottom to humility and there's no lid on love and that there's power when we choose to be humble.

02:12.519 --> 02:17.906
Today we're gonna look at the power of Jesus and next week we're gonna look at the purpose

02:18.242 --> 02:18.843
of Jesus.

02:19.904 --> 02:32.736
The interesting thing to me about the local church is different than any other organization, any other institution, any other movement, any other gathering is the movement of the local church is supernatural.

02:32.756 --> 02:40.064
That scripture says that there is something supernatural when the people of Jesus come together on mission together.

02:40.444 --> 02:42.946
And in that is power.

02:43.006 --> 02:46.610
There's the power of scripture, the Bible, the Word of God,

02:46.722 --> 02:51.569
There's the power of the gospel, the truth of Jesus and who He is and how He changes us.

02:51.949 --> 03:03.365
There's the power of how we come together in alignment, a group of people coming together saying, hey, we're gonna align around a mission, the gifts God's given us, we're gonna use them to point people to Him.

03:03.405 --> 03:04.486
There's power in that.

03:05.447 --> 03:11.055
But at the heart of the power of the local church is the power of the Holy Spirit.

03:12.076 --> 03:14.700
And that's what I wanna talk a little bit about today.

03:14.880 --> 03:16.242
If you're new to church,

03:16.418 --> 03:19.543
You may have heard the term father, son, Holy Spirit.

03:19.563 --> 03:20.624
We had a baptism day.

03:20.644 --> 03:24.370
Somebody was baptized in the name of the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit.

03:24.390 --> 03:27.575
Because we believe that there is one God, three persons.

03:28.076 --> 03:32.823
Father, God the Father, God the Son, that's Jesus, and the Holy Spirit.

03:33.604 --> 03:34.926
And who is the Holy Spirit?

03:34.946 --> 03:36.509
And how does the Holy Spirit work?

03:36.529 --> 03:42.578
Well, the Holy Spirit, actually, when you read scripture, empowered Jesus when he walked this earth.

03:43.106 --> 03:46.951
that when Jesus is baptized, you actually can see that the Holy Spirit is present there.

03:47.732 --> 03:54.139
When Jesus is tempted in the desert, you can see that it's the Holy Spirit that is strengthening him and walking with him.

03:55.080 --> 03:58.364
And Jesus died and rose again and then returned to heaven.

03:58.444 --> 04:03.010
And he says, I left with those of you who choose to follow me, the Holy Spirit.

04:03.070 --> 04:07.155
Just like I'm filled with the Holy Spirit, you can be filled with the Holy Spirit.

04:07.175 --> 04:09.978
He actually says this just before he ascends to heaven.

04:09.998 --> 04:13.042
He says this, but in fact, it is best for you

04:13.250 --> 04:17.716
He says in the disciples, it's best for you that I go away, Jesus said.

04:18.477 --> 04:21.962
Because if I don't, the advocate won't come.

04:21.982 --> 04:22.783
Who is the advocate?

04:22.823 --> 04:24.726
He's talking about the Holy Spirit.

04:25.286 --> 04:27.570
Sometimes the word advocate is used.

04:28.110 --> 04:28.711
Why is that?

04:28.791 --> 04:31.996
Because the Holy Spirit advocates for Jesus in your life.

04:32.717 --> 04:36.181
He says, if I do go away, then I'll send him to you.

04:36.422 --> 04:42.610
And when he comes, the Holy Spirit, he's gonna convict the world of sin and of God's righteousness.

04:43.138 --> 04:44.279
and of coming judgment.

04:44.319 --> 04:52.649
Maybe you're here and you would say, hey, I wouldn't even call myself a Jesus follower, but I've definitely felt conviction before around sin, around brokenness.

04:52.669 --> 04:58.555
I've definitely found conviction around the fact that, man, God is right and God is good and I need to be made right with him.

04:58.595 --> 05:00.077
That's what the Holy Spirit does.

05:01.659 --> 05:09.267
And he says, later on in the passage, Jesus says, there is so much more I wanna tell you, but you can't bear it right now.

05:09.327 --> 05:12.050
But when the spirit of truth, the Holy Spirit comes,

05:12.162 --> 05:13.864
He's gonna guide you in all truth.

05:14.244 --> 05:18.228
He will not speak on his own, but he will tell you what he has heard.

05:19.349 --> 05:20.990
And he will tell you about the future.

05:21.571 --> 05:27.997
And this Holy Spirit, he will bring me glory by telling you whatever he receives from me.

05:28.858 --> 05:33.682
Whatever the Holy Spirit receives from me, Jesus says, he's gonna tell you, he's gonna relay it to you.

05:33.762 --> 05:35.164
He's gonna give it to you.

05:35.664 --> 05:37.466
All that belongs to the Father's mind.

05:37.486 --> 05:41.810
And this is why I said, the Spirit will tell you whatever he receives from me.

05:43.202 --> 05:47.749
When Scripture talks about the Holy Spirit as an advocate, the Holy Spirit isn't an advocate for you.

05:47.789 --> 05:49.411
He's an advocate for Jesus in you.

05:50.253 --> 05:53.217
The Holy Spirit is an advocate for Jesus in your life.

05:53.277 --> 05:55.741
He puts the spotlight of Jesus on your life.

05:55.801 --> 05:57.965
He wants you to know what Jesus wants for you.

05:58.005 --> 06:00.288
He wants you to know what Jesus would say to you.

06:02.311 --> 06:09.823
And when we talk about being a church that every community needs, can you be a church without the power of the Holy Spirit?

06:11.405 --> 06:11.986
Well,

06:12.066 --> 06:14.289
I'll tell you, lots of things can gather a crowd.

06:15.470 --> 06:18.995
You can build a church on a lot of things, a lot of gatherings.

06:19.736 --> 06:21.578
You can get a crowd around politics.

06:22.339 --> 06:24.381
You can get a crowd around being controversial.

06:25.102 --> 06:29.348
You can get a crowd around saying all the things that you're against.

06:29.708 --> 06:31.590
You can get a crowd around entertainment.

06:32.211 --> 06:37.618
There are lots of ways to build a crowd, but it's the Holy Spirit that builds a church.

06:38.818 --> 06:45.489
and scripture is very clear on that, the very beginning of the church is when the Holy Spirit arrives on the scene.

06:46.451 --> 06:58.590
Jesus has returned to heaven, he just said, what I just shared with you in John 16, and he tells the disciples to wait for the power of the Holy Spirit, and they wait for 50 days, and they're all hanging out together in this room.

06:58.610 --> 07:01.675
I'm sure they weren't in there the whole 50 days, because that wouldn't smell good.

07:01.695 --> 07:05.682
I'm sure they went out and got some food and came back, but they're in this room,

07:06.786 --> 07:15.039
It says, suddenly there was a sound from heaven, like the roaring of a mighty windstorm, and it filled the house where they were sitting.

07:16.161 --> 07:22.351
And then what looked like flames or tongues of fire appeared and settled on each of them.

07:22.491 --> 07:31.666
And everyone present was filled with the Holy Spirit and began speaking in other languages as the Holy Spirit gave them this ability.

07:32.706 --> 07:36.670
See this group of disciples, they all knew about Jesus.

07:36.730 --> 07:38.151
They all seen him die.

07:38.231 --> 07:40.494
They all saw him come back to life.

07:40.514 --> 07:42.476
They believed he was the Son of God.

07:43.637 --> 07:46.840
And they wanted to tell the world, but they didn't have the words to do it.

07:48.241 --> 07:51.865
And it's the Holy Spirit that gave them the ability to speak different languages.

07:51.945 --> 08:01.074
This is the birth of the early church that the church began because of the power of the Holy Spirit.

08:02.754 --> 08:10.023
And you see the thing about the Holy Spirit that you see here is the Holy Spirit makes faith not just true, but real.

08:11.405 --> 08:14.088
That for the disciples, it wasn't just something they'd seen.

08:14.128 --> 08:21.658
And they said, well, we know it's true he died and we know it's true he rose again, but all of a sudden it's become so much more real to them.

08:22.599 --> 08:28.627
And they start preaching and all these people, their lives are being changed and they're all choosing to follow Jesus with their lives.

08:28.947 --> 08:31.250
And the beginning of the church movement,

08:31.330 --> 08:38.919
begins to roll out, and we're here today because of what happened in Acts 2, the power of the Holy Spirit.

08:41.702 --> 08:43.604
But here's the thing about the Holy Spirit.

08:43.784 --> 08:51.793
Depending on your background, when I talk about the Holy Spirit, for some of you, it makes you uncomfortable.

08:54.116 --> 08:57.660
Because maybe for you, you're like, this is exactly what I thought about Christians.

08:57.680 --> 08:59.282
They're so weird.

09:01.986 --> 09:03.127
talking about the Holy Spirit.

09:03.528 --> 09:14.200
And then there are others of you who would say, man, I come from a church background and we talk more Father, Son, Holy Bible than we did Father, Son, Holy Spirit.

09:15.922 --> 09:18.706
And this kind of makes me uncomfortable.

09:20.408 --> 09:22.190
And that's the background I come from.

09:23.711 --> 09:27.256
Or maybe you're here today and you're like, man, I love it.

09:27.276 --> 09:29.298
Let's all talk about the Holy Spirit.

09:29.442 --> 09:32.365
And my question for you is just make sure you're not super weird either.

09:32.405 --> 09:34.568
I get that too.

09:36.510 --> 09:44.139
But when it comes to the Holy Spirit, there's a part of some of us that struggles to kind of wrestle with who is the Holy Spirit?

09:44.159 --> 09:45.661
And how does the Holy Spirit work?

09:46.061 --> 09:49.946
And what would it mean if I leaned more into the Holy Spirit?

09:49.966 --> 09:52.329
That kind of makes me nervous.

09:54.771 --> 09:57.074
And part of that is because

09:57.410 --> 10:04.238
When the Holy Spirit works in our lives, sometimes it means that we're not in control.

10:06.800 --> 10:13.087
I want to share with you a journey that I've been on recently around this and it started five years ago.

10:15.390 --> 10:26.322
Five years ago, I was in my basement and it was the heart of COVID, not my favorite time.

10:27.810 --> 10:36.300
I was praying and I really felt God saying, I want Connects us to lean more into the person of the Holy Spirit.

10:38.702 --> 10:44.148
And I said, okay, just so you know, God, this makes me uncomfortable, but I get it.

10:45.850 --> 10:50.535
And so a number of things happened in our church that have happened over the last five years.

10:50.656 --> 10:52.838
We've leaned more into the Holy Spirit.

10:52.918 --> 10:56.402
You've probably noticed if you've been with us a long time that our services

10:56.674 --> 10:57.855
have had some changes.

10:58.336 --> 11:06.684
There are a lot of general sense of trying to create an accessible encounter for people who are new to faith and encounter with the Holy Spirit.

11:07.104 --> 11:16.814
I've taught Beginner's Guide to the Holy Spirit, a series that came out of that, another series called Invisible God, and really leaning into that.

11:18.636 --> 11:21.318
There's another part of the conversation that happened.

11:23.200 --> 11:25.202
24 years ago,

11:25.890 --> 11:38.706
I was part of a church that at a certain point, God did something really powerful where they set aside a week to lean into the presence of God.

11:41.009 --> 11:44.033
And I said, God, are you saying we're supposed to do that at our church?

11:46.876 --> 11:54.866
And because I said, I don't want to just take something that happened in some other church and try to force it on our church.

11:55.874 --> 11:57.015
I didn't hear anything.

11:58.657 --> 12:06.145
So I said, OK, God, if you want this, people in the church are going to have to come to me and tell me they want it.

12:08.067 --> 12:15.535
If you want us to lean more into the presence of God and what the Holy Spirit wants to do in our lives, they're going to have to come to me.

12:16.136 --> 12:17.938
I'm not going to force this on anybody.

12:18.679 --> 12:19.680
That was five years ago.

12:21.962 --> 12:25.266
And over the course of those five years, there was a moment where

12:25.890 --> 12:31.217
Somebody came to me and said, hey, God told me, which is dangerous, by the way.

12:32.499 --> 12:40.170
If someone comes to you and says, God told me, especially if they say, God told me you're supposed to marry me, be very, very careful of that.

12:43.514 --> 12:49.042
And they said, there's a pastor who you know, and God told me that that pastor is supposed to pray for you.

12:51.714 --> 12:57.724
And I was at a conference in the UK and here I see this pastor who's also Canadian standing at the front praying.

12:59.647 --> 13:03.753
And I went up and I was like, I just know God's gonna say something I don't wanna hear.

13:04.174 --> 13:07.098
And I was like, okay, you're supposed to pray for me.

13:09.262 --> 13:19.378
And he prayed for me and he said, I think God's asking you the question, would you lead your church in a direction even if it was uncomfortable for you?

13:22.530 --> 13:23.871
I was like two, three years ago.

13:25.693 --> 13:31.179
In this past year, the staff prayed over me at a staff retreat spontaneously, and I was like, God, is this the moment?

13:31.199 --> 13:34.043
Are we supposed to lean into God?

13:34.103 --> 13:35.124
Is that what this is?

13:35.184 --> 13:37.947
And it wasn't.

13:39.969 --> 13:41.070
Five years have passed.

13:44.314 --> 13:51.922
And I was up here at the front one day, on Sunday, and man, people were coming to the front.

13:52.578 --> 13:54.280
and their lives were being changed.

13:59.147 --> 14:02.813
And I was just like, oh, this is unbelievable.

14:04.435 --> 14:10.564
God was appearing to somebody in a dream and people were begging for Bibles and I was like, I've never seen this.

14:12.306 --> 14:20.658
And the person next to me says, have you heard this podcast and carrying you off the founder of this church recently

14:20.994 --> 14:26.179
did a podcast where the church where God really showed up in a powerful way.

14:26.219 --> 14:34.528
And I wasn't listening to it because I was afraid that would force me to do the thing from five years ago.

14:34.608 --> 14:36.950
Like if I listen to this, God might tell me we have to do it.

14:38.672 --> 14:39.553
So I'm not gonna listen.

14:41.795 --> 14:44.157
And she said, have you listened to it?

14:44.237 --> 14:48.882
I said, no, she said, if we would ever do something like that at this church, I would be all in.

14:51.682 --> 14:55.966
And then I ran into someone else who has a similar background to mine on our staff team.

14:56.867 --> 14:59.089
And they said, well, we ever do something like this at our church.

14:59.109 --> 15:01.211
I'm like, I guess I have to listen to this podcast now.

15:04.354 --> 15:11.642
And I had someone else and I listened to the podcast and it was so similar to what I'd experienced 24 years ago.

15:14.725 --> 15:17.067
And I said to God, what do I do?

15:19.109 --> 15:20.210
And I didn't hear anything.

15:22.114 --> 15:26.441
And when I talk about hearing from God, I want you to know I'm not saying that because I'm super spiritual and you're not.

15:26.541 --> 15:27.743
I'm just a regular person.

15:27.803 --> 15:28.824
I got a house here in Barry.

15:28.885 --> 15:29.986
I live the same life you live.

15:32.190 --> 15:33.031
I didn't hear anything.

15:33.111 --> 15:34.393
I was desperate to hear.

15:36.717 --> 15:42.606
And so I decided on the Labor Day weekend that I would fast and pray until God spoke to me.

15:44.749 --> 15:50.418
And on the Monday of Labor Day weekend, I was preparing the message on the prodigal son.

15:50.722 --> 15:52.064
that I preached a couple of weeks ago.

16:01.596 --> 16:03.559
And I was reading about the older son.

16:04.160 --> 16:11.109
And if you were here and you heard that message, it broke me for you.

16:16.897 --> 16:17.938
And I've been crying

16:19.906 --> 16:21.228
over two weeks for you.

16:25.052 --> 16:26.113
God wants to meet you.

16:29.678 --> 16:30.779
And I'm crying everywhere.

16:31.800 --> 16:32.962
And I'm fine, like.

16:33.002 --> 16:37.788
I feel fine.

16:37.948 --> 16:38.789
I'm the healthy.

16:39.189 --> 16:41.452
I'm probably the healthiest I've been.

16:41.472 --> 16:42.593
I feel great.

16:42.713 --> 16:46.017
I don't cry all day long, but I cry about this.

16:48.981 --> 16:49.842
I got to thinking about

16:51.426 --> 16:52.968
Just you encountering Jesus.

16:54.630 --> 16:57.173
I'm crying in front of 50 people in a restaurant.

17:05.542 --> 17:08.806
And the reason for the tears, I don't like this.

17:10.789 --> 17:18.898
It's because the Holy Spirit when He's speaking to me makes me cry so that I know that I'm not in control and to humble me because I hate it.

17:22.498 --> 17:27.526
And so I went to the leadership team here and I went to the elders.

17:29.729 --> 17:37.281
And I said, I think God's asking us to set aside a time at this church to seek the presence of God.

17:39.464 --> 17:44.412
And that's all.

17:44.432 --> 17:46.094
What is the Holy Spirit saying?

17:47.737 --> 17:51.122
I think Jesus is saying that he has something to say to you.

17:52.642 --> 17:57.008
Personally, I don't know what that is.

17:59.872 --> 18:03.397
And I think that Jesus has something that he wants to say to us as a church.

18:07.924 --> 18:21.042
And I said to the leadership team, hey, what would it mean to do this in January because the fall is so busy if we were to gather people together and seek the presence of God

18:21.346 --> 18:23.128
and figure out what that even looks like.

18:24.449 --> 18:25.711
I said, we're all so busy.

18:25.831 --> 18:27.453
January is probably the best time.

18:28.414 --> 18:29.235
And they said, no.

18:32.238 --> 18:36.743
They said, if God wants to meet us, we want to do this as quickly as we can.

18:39.586 --> 18:42.349
And so we've been praying.

18:42.909 --> 18:50.898
We've been back gathering scripture from a number of people we trust in our church and praying around it and what it says and figuring out what this looks like.

18:52.802 --> 19:18.207
And we've decided that from Tuesday, October the 21st to the 24th, we're going to host something, we're going to call it sacred homecoming for all the older brothers and all the younger brothers and everyone in between to come home and sit with God their father and has the Holy Spirit what Jesus wants to say to you.

19:20.549 --> 19:21.170
And you're like,

19:21.634 --> 19:23.957
What church is this?

19:23.977 --> 19:24.998
We don't do this here.

19:25.058 --> 19:25.819
I know.

19:28.142 --> 19:30.044
And you're like, this makes me uncomfortable.

19:32.026 --> 19:33.608
And I would say welcome to the club.

19:38.274 --> 19:39.355
What is this going to look like?

19:39.875 --> 19:41.838
We're shutting down all programming that week.

19:41.858 --> 19:42.879
There will be no groups.

19:42.959 --> 19:44.220
There will be no student ministry.

19:44.241 --> 19:45.142
There will be no alpha.

19:45.162 --> 19:46.103
There will be no anything.

19:46.623 --> 19:48.946
This is highly inconvenient for us.

19:51.746 --> 19:53.128
And I think that's on purpose.

19:54.710 --> 19:57.894
That God wants to see if we would prioritize presence with Him.

19:59.576 --> 20:02.901
We're going to have services every morning and every evening.

20:05.164 --> 20:06.165
And what will they look like?

20:06.185 --> 20:09.129
Well, we're still deciding some of that, but they will look different.

20:09.970 --> 20:10.911
There'll be communion.

20:10.931 --> 20:11.772
There'll be prayer.

20:11.973 --> 20:12.934
There'll be silence.

20:13.014 --> 20:14.696
There'll be an opportunity to be prayed for.

20:14.756 --> 20:16.619
There'll be space for you to hear from God.

20:17.380 --> 20:19.122
And what I want to ask you to do

20:19.362 --> 20:25.710
What I want to challenge you to do is make arrangements to be there as often as you can.

20:27.633 --> 20:33.400
We're going to have a 15 day reading plan to prepare us for that, to get your heart ready to meet with God.

20:35.563 --> 20:40.489
And I would ask that you would come with an open heart.

20:43.072 --> 20:47.538
And if I have ever earned chips with you, I'm cashing them all.

20:56.258 --> 20:59.503
This will be much more presence over Polish.

21:01.386 --> 21:03.790
It'll be about invitation, not manipulation.

21:05.853 --> 21:08.798
And I pray that you would be open to what God might do in your life.

21:08.818 --> 21:14.667
And to give you just a sneak peek of what we're hearing, because we've collected all this scripture from people that we're praying through.

21:16.550 --> 21:21.718
There are themes of return, themes of repentance and themes of renewal.

21:21.818 --> 21:24.242
I know they all start with our, I didn't do that.

21:27.490 --> 21:32.475
And if you're like, wow, this feels inconvenient for my life.

21:32.795 --> 21:33.936
I got to get babysitters.

21:33.976 --> 21:35.698
We got to figure out who's going to be here when.

21:36.499 --> 21:39.021
How am I going to get to some of this stuff I want to be there?

21:39.221 --> 21:43.085
Or I don't really know if I want to do this, or that's a busy time for me at work.

21:43.606 --> 21:44.026
I get it.

21:44.106 --> 21:46.588
It's inconvenient.

21:46.608 --> 21:56.498
I think God is asking, are you willing to do what it takes to seek God's presence and hear Jesus by the power of the Spirit?

21:58.402 --> 22:00.185
would you be willing to do what it takes?

22:02.088 --> 22:10.341
Because if we are going to be the church that this community needs, they can't just come here and find us.

